## Task Management
- Check `docs/tasks/open/` first for matching work before starting substantive changes
- If a matching task exists, resume from `Left Off At` and use `Attempts` to avoid retrying failed approaches
- If no task exists for substantive work, create one from `docs/tasks/TEMPLATE.md`
- Keep `Attempts` append-only
- End implementation in `needs verification`, not `done`
- Follow `docs/WORKFLOW.md` for full task lifecycle

## Constraints
<!-- Additional constraints for agent behavior -->
- Read code before proposing edits
- Fix root causes, not symptoms
- Execute in small verifiable steps; stop on failed verification

## Git Workflow
<!-- Define your branching and commit strategy -->
- Work directly on the current branch unless explicitly asked to create worktrees

